claim.claim-text:
11. A method comprising:
receiving a request for an Internet Protocol version 6 (IPv6) prefix from a media access gateway;
assigning the IPv6 prefix to a mobile station through a local mobility anchor (LMA) by using proxy mobile IPv6; and
sending the IPv6 address to the mobile station;
wherein the method is implemented at a Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP) server or an Authentication, Authorization and Accounting (AAA) server.

15. A communications system comprising:
a plurality of base stations in communication with a plurality of mobile stations;
an access router in communication with the base stations and a prefix issuing party;
wherein communications between the access router and the prefix issuing party are routed through a home agent by using proxy mobile IPv6,
wherein the prefix issuing party issues an address prefix to at least some of the mobile stations;
wherein a media access gateway (MAG) advertises the address prefix;
wherein at least some of the mobile stations use the address prefixes to create an internet protocol version 6 (IPv6) address.
